From: Chunguang Xu <chunguang.xu@shopee.com>
Date: Tue, 11 Jun 2024 18:02:08 +0800
Subject: nvme: avoid double free special payload
Patch-mainline: v6.10-rc4
Git-commit: e5d574ab37f5f2e7937405613d9b1a724811e5ad
References: git-fixes CVE-2024-41073 bsc#1228635

If a discard request needs to be retried, and that retry may fail before
a new special payload is added, a double free will result. Clear the
RQF_SPECIAL_LOAD when the request is cleaned.

Signed-off-by: Chunguang Xu <chunguang.xu@shopee.com>
Reviewed-by: Sagi Grimberg <sagi@grimberg.me>
Reviewed-by: Max Gurtovoy <mgurtovoy@nvidia.com>
Signed-off-by: Keith Busch <kbusch@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Daniel Wagner <dwagner@suse.de>
---
 drivers/nvme/host/core.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/nvme/host/core.c
+++ b/drivers/nvme/host/core.c
@@ -953,6 +953,7 @@ void nvme_cleanup_cmd(struct request *re
 			clear_bit_unlock(0, &ctrl->discard_page_busy);
 		else
 			kfree(bvec_virt(&req->special_vec));
+		req->rq_flags &= ~RQF_SPECIAL_PAYLOAD;
 	}
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(nvme_cleanup_cmd);
